00:14:26,093 --> 00:14:28,996
and you don't have the right tools to do it, it's pretty overwhelming

296
00:14:29,136 --> 00:14:30,758
and it's going to be very hard to analyze.

297
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:33,962
But it's the...

298
00:14:35,384 --> 00:14:38,251
it's like the step one to be able to train

299
00:14:38,531 --> 00:14:41,016
an artificial intelligence model to learn stuff.

300
00:14:41,518 --> 00:14:43,482
So one of the things that we found is that

301
00:14:44,424 --> 00:14:45,085
in order to train.

302
00:14:46,035 --> 00:14:51,018
an artificial intelligence system, basically what you need is data and information.

303
00:14:51,819 --> 00:14:56,001
So that, like, classified information. I know that the user managed to pick this word.

304
00:14:56,181 --> 00:15:00,844
I know that the user performed well. I know that the user hit the milestone.

305
00:15:00,924 --> 00:15:06,567
I know that the user missed a turn or missed a quest or missed something.

306
00:15:07,367 --> 00:15:10,969
And basically, all that data comes from your QA team.

307
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:13,691
As you are building the game, as they are playing the game,

308
00:15:14,071 --> 00:15:15,392
they create a ton of data.

309
00:15:15,632 --> 00:15:19,113
So they're actually creating your training set for you.

310
00:15:19,593 --> 00:15:22,414
And this is really enough just to bootstrap the whole process.

311
00:15:23,335 --> 00:15:24,275
You need a ton of data,

312
00:15:24,455 --> 00:15:27,356
and the system really learns along the way.

313
00:15:27,716 --> 00:15:30,317
It needs to be bootstrapped, and QA does that just fine.

314
00:15:31,798 --> 00:15:35,239
And what's the ultimate result of data, of that much data?

315
00:15:35,259 --> 00:15:37,420
It's really about figuring out whether it's a hot dog or not.

316
00:15:38,089 --> 00:15:41,893
So if you have watched Silicon Valley history, what it does,

317
00:15:42,253 --> 00:15:44,776
it tells you if that thing is there or not.

318
00:15:45,136 --> 00:15:46,898
So in Silicon Valley, hot dog, not hot dog.

319
00:15:46,978 --> 00:15:50,883
In our case, it's beat the boss, not beat the boss.

320
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:55,648
Lost many lives, not lost them before he got to the boss

