00:15:59,892 --> 00:16:04,477
he always drifts too much and ends up hitting the curve on the Formula 1 game,

323
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:08,520
it's all those information that you are able to identify through the data to

324
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:13,965
figure out what kind of a player you have in front of you and what was his

325
00:16:14,005 --> 00:16:16,087
trajectory through the journey in the game.

326
00:16:19,067 --> 00:16:22,328
Data is really about, it's basically probabilities.

327
00:16:22,868 --> 00:16:26,369
The engine looks at the data that you give him,

328
00:16:26,409 --> 00:16:29,130
and what's really cool is that once you've had all those data

329
00:16:29,170 --> 00:16:31,130
pre-processed, you don't need them anymore.

330
00:16:31,351 --> 00:16:35,432
Basically, you have your model, and you can just, in real time,

331
00:16:35,532 --> 00:16:38,592
analyze the data of any player and tell, hey, OK,

332
00:16:38,632 --> 00:16:40,413
so he's taking the turn just fine.

333
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:44,454
He is changing gears at the right time.

334
00:16:44,954 --> 00:16:49,999
he is not speeding too much on that line because there is a turn coming up,

335
00:16:50,419 --> 00:16:56,625
he is braking at the right, about the right, the right position, and you can analyze all this information and make it very holistic.

